13 "Part 6B
14 20-3-518.8.
15 (a) As used in this part, the term:
16 (1) 'Animal shelter' means any facility operated by or under contract for the state or any
17 county, municipal corporation, or political subdivision of the state or by a nonprofit
18 organization for the purpose of impounding or harboring seized, stray, homeless,
19 abandoned, or unwanted dogs, cats, or other animals.
20 (2) 'Board' means the State Veterinary Education Board for Shelter Medicine and Pet
21 Sterilization created under Code Section 20-3-518.9.
22 (3) 'Nonprofit organization' means an organization which is exempt from taxation under
23 the provisions of Section 501(c)(3) of the United States Internal Revenue Code.
24 (4) 'Nonprofit pet sterilization clinic' means a veterinary facility that exclusively offers
25 pet sterilization services and which is a nonprofit organization.
26 (5) 'Pet sterilization services' means procedures that meet or exceed veterinary medical
27 standards of care in providing sterilization of dogs, cats, and pet rabbits.
28 (6) 'Shelter medicine' means veterinary practices used to manage the health of
29 populations of animals handled by animal shelters.
30 (7) 'Veterinary facility' shall have the same meaning as provided in Code Section
31 43-50-3.
32 20-3-518.9.
33 (a) There shall be a State Veterinary Education Board for Shelter Medicine and Pet
34 Sterilization which shall consist of:
35 (1) The Commissioner of Agriculture or his or her designee;
36 (2) The dean of the College of Veterinary Medicine of the University of Georgia or his
37 or her designee;
