49 (b) Any vacancies on the board shall be filled in the same manner as the original
50 appointment.
51 (c) The board shall elect annually a chairperson and a vice chairperson to serve in the
52 absence or inability of the chairperson. The board shall meet at least once each year at
53 such time and place as may be fixed by the board. Special meetings shall be held upon the
54 call of the chairperson. Three members of the board shall constitute a quorum for the
55 transaction of business. No official action shall be taken by the board except upon the
56 affirmative vote of at least three members of the board.
57 (d) The board shall be attached to the Department of Agriculture for administrative
58 purposes only, pursuant to Code Section 50-4-3.
